President Trump signed an executive order to bring new hope to Americans suffering from kidney disease. The order aims to increase the supply of kidney-available transplants and improve prevention and treatment of kidney disease. It also supports individuals who donate kidneys by granting them reimbursement for expenses associated with organ donation. The order will establish more transparent and enforceable rules for organ procurement organizations to ensure that kidneys reach waiting patients as quickly as possible. The goal is to increase the number of Americans receiving kidneys and other organ transplants, ultimately saving lives and reducing healthcare costs. The executive order also encourages the development of an artificial kidney. The President highlighted the personal stories of individuals affected by kidney disease, emphasizing the importance of improving kidney health for all Americans.